CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 5, 1945, pg. 26 reads: "Tots Celebrate Birthday - Little Diane Blackwell, two-year-old daughter of Mr. and Mrs. R.L. Blackwell, celebrated her birthday last week with a party at the home of her aunt and uncle on Bryn Mawr Road. Sharing honors with Diane was Florence Garrett of Bentley Drive, whose birthday was on the same date.  Guests were: Patricia and Arbustus Cathie, Diane Walker, Fredricka, Catherine and Evelyn Reynolds, Marvin and Eleanor Randall, Joyce Walker, Pearl Broadnax, Jacqueline and Oliver Horsley,  Arnetta Lewis, Hattie Williams, Gladys and Junior Henderson and Madelyn Formley. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of birthday party, including Florence Garrett, Patricia Cathie, Arbustus Cathie, Diane Walker, Fredricka Reynolds, Catherine Reynolds, Evelyn Reynolds, Marvin Randall, Eleanor Randall, Joyce Walker, Pearl Broadnax, Jacqueline Horsley, Oliver Horsley, Arnetta Lewis, Hattie Williams, Gladys Henderson, Junior Henderson, Madelyn Formley, gathered around Diana Blackwell second from right, at long table with cake, in home on Bryn Mawr Road
